# Chest X-Ray Pathology Detection

A deep learning pipeline for multi-label pulmonary disease classification using the 
NIH Chest X-Ray dataset. This project trains and compares three architectures — a 
custom CNN, DenseNet-121 with transfer learning, and a Vision Transformer (ViT) — 
then combines them into a soft voting ensemble. Monte Carlo Dropout is applied for 
uncertainty quantification, and Grad-CAM visualizations are generated for model 
interpretability.

---

## Project Overview

- **Dataset:** NIH Chest X-Ray (112,120 images, 14 pathology classes)
- **Task:** Multi-label image classification
- **Models:** Custom CNN, DenseNet-121, Vision Transformer (ViT), Soft Voting Ensemble
- **Uncertainty:** Monte Carlo Dropout
- **Interpretability:** Grad-CAM heatmap visualizations
- **Framework:** PyTorch

---

## Repository Structure
```
chest-xray-pathology-detection/
├── data/
│   └── preprocess.py          # Resizing, normalization, augmentation
├── models/
│   ├── custom_cnn.py          # Baseline CNN built from scratch
│   ├── densenet121.py         # DenseNet-121 with transfer learning
│   └── vit.py                 # Vision Transformer
├── ensemble/
│   └── soft_voting.py         # Combines model outputs via probability averaging
├── uncertainty/
│   └── mc_dropout.py          # Monte Carlo Dropout inference
├── visualization/
│   └── gradcam.py             # Grad-CAM heatmap generation
├── train.py                   # Training loop
├── evaluate.py                # AUC-ROC, F1, precision, recall
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## Models

| Model | Description |
|---|---|
| Custom CNN | 3-4 layer CNN trained from scratch, serves as baseline |
| DenseNet-121 | Pretrained on ImageNet, fine-tuned on NIH dataset |
| ViT | Attention-based transformer applied to image patches |
| Ensemble | Soft voting across all three model probability outputs |

---

## Evaluation Metrics

- AUC-ROC per pathology class (primary metric, compared against CheXNet benchmark)
- F1-Score
- Precision and Recall
- Uncertainty correlation analysis (MC Dropout variance vs. misclassification rate)

